scopeContent.description:
1) 'Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-18. Group, Mr J R Benson kneeling at left of picture, a woman with snakes turned round her arms & lady sitting at base of statue with one arm raised clasping pillar. Woman lying on ground in front of Mr Benson, other figures lying about on ground'. 3cm x 3cm.

2) 'Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-19. Group, Mr J R Benson kneeling with hands resting on statue, a woman with snake over her shoulders standing by him, a woman standing on dais at right of picture holding long staff in right hand. Mr Kneightley standing high up at back holding staff in right hand, figures with snakes twined round them in various parts of picture'. 3cm x 3cm.

3) 'Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-2. Group, Mr Keightley standing high up at back holding staff in right hand, woman with snakes twined round her arms kneeling at base of statue. Other figures with snakes twined round their arms stretched stretched towards Mr Keightley'. 3cm x 3cm.

4) 'Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size, No 43002-21. Group, Mr F R Benson standing on raised platform at back holding sword, two figures lying dead on ground by him. Crowd of women standing at left of pictures'. 3cm x 3cm.

5) 'Photograph of The Orestean Trilogy, whole plate size No 43002-9. Group, Miss Gertrude Scott kneeling in centre, a man standing at right with left hand raised & right hand holding staff, two men standing at left of picture. A man sitting on steps at back'. 3cm x 3cm.

6) 'Photograph of King Lear, whole plate size, No 43001-1. Group, man lying full length on ground, a man in centre supporting Mr Benson. A woman with hood over head pointing to them, a man standing by her holding her arm'. 3cm x 3cm.

7) 'Photograph of 'King Lear', whole plate size No 43001-2. Group, Mr Benson wearing crown sitting at top of steps, Mrs Benson standing with with one foot on bottom step. Miss Mabel Moore standing at the other side of steps with a man holding paper, other figures grouped round'. 3cm x 3cm.

8) 'Photograph of 'King Lear', whole plate size No 43001-3. Group, Mr Benson at top of steps bending forward, Mrs Benson half sitting on steps. Mabel Moore holding paper in left hand standing at the other of steps watching her, other figures grouped round'. 3cm x 3cm.

9) 'Photograph of Miss Nancy Price, cabinet size, No 43374-14, full length standing profile in evening dress, resting right arm on top of lounge'. 3cm x 2cm.

10) 'Photograph of Miss Nancy Price, cabinet size, No 43374-15, full length sitting on lounge playing guitar, head leaning towards her right shoulder'. 3cm x 2cm.

11) 'Photograph of Miss Nancy Price, cabinet size No 43374-17, full length standing almost full face, resting left hand on hat on table'. 3cm x 2cm.

12) 'Photograph of Miss Nancy Price, cabinet size No 43374-18, full length standing three quarter face, hat half resting on table & holding it in both her hands'. 3cm x 2cm.

13) 'Photograph of Miss Billie Burke, panel size No 42918-1, half length profile, wearing Grecian dress, holding spray of large lilies in front of figure'. 6cm x 3cm.

14) 'Photograph of Miss Billie Burke, panel size No 42918-2, three quarter length profile, wearing Grecian dress, holding spray of large lilies in front of figure in both hands'. Photograph missing.

15) 'Photograph of Miss Billie Burke, panel size No 42918-3, three quarter length, wearing Empire gown, three quarter face, resting hands on large palm pot & resting face on hands'. 6cm x 3cm.

16) 'Photograph of Miss Billie Burke, cabinet size No 42918-4, head & bust, three quarter face smiling, holding open fan to chin with right hand'. 3cm x 2cm.
